name: treatment of used vegetable cooking oil, purification | used vegetable cooking oil, purified | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/9242/documentation

Treated vegetable oil consists of 93.7% triglycerides and 6.7% fatty acid methyl ester. Process refers to the acid-catalysed esterification of free fatty acids and includes water removal, glycerine washing and methanol recovery. ;Data from Quebec dataset have been added to this GLO dataset to reflect Quebec particularity of the technology and site location (non urban area). 



This process includes the collection of waste vegetable oil and delivery to the treatment plant, treatment for impurities and water removal, conditioning and storage of the oil. Treatment of effluents is taken into account. Includes also the gross calorific value of the biomass and the carbon dioxide credit. System boundary is at the oil refining facility.
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/383:Materials recovery/3830:Materials recovery
